nglish, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Bendeng","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: probably a variant of   Bindon  .  Compare  Bendon  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Bindon","meanings":["English and Irish: habitational name from Bindon in Axmouth, Devon or Bindon in Wool, Dorset. A member of the family settled in Ireland, and the name <i>Bindon</i> became fairly common in County Clare."]},{"name":"Bendon","meanings":["English:","habitational name from one of four places: Benenden or the lost place called Begginden, both in Kent; Building End in Chrishall in Essex; or Bandons in Anstey in Hertfordshire. Benenden is named from the Old English personal name <i>Bionna</i> + <i>-ing-</i> denoting association with + <i>denn</i> ‘woodland pasture’.","(southwestern): variant of   Bindon  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Bendeng was born about 1130 as the son of de Bendeng. He married Gunnora about 1165. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died about 1197, at the age of 69."},"et":{"about 1130–about 1197":"umbes 1130–umbes 1197","1129–1190":"1129–1190","1130–1197":"1130–1197","1070–1158":"1070–1158","1170–1229":"1170–1229","–Male":"Surnud","1190":"1190","1129":"1129","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1158":"1158","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","about 1165":"umbes 1165","about 1130":"umbes 1130","1170":"1170","about 1197":"umbes 1197","1229":"1229","1070":"1070","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1130–about 1197":"noin 1130–noin 1197","1129–1190":"1129–1190","1130–1197":"1130–1197","1070–1158":"1070–1158","1170–1229":"1170–1229","–Male":"Kuollut","1190":"1190","1129":"1129","about 1170":"noin 1170","1158":"1158","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","about 1165":"noin 1165","about 1130":"noin 1130","1170":"1170","about 1197":"noin 1197","1229":"1229","1070":"1070","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1130–about 1197":"environ 1130–environ 1197","1129–1190":"1129–1190","1130–1197":"1130–1197","1070–1158":"1070–1158","1170–1229":"1170–1229","–Male":"Décédé","1190":"1190","1129":"1129","about 1170":"environ 1170","1158":"1158","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","about 1165":"environ 1165","about 1130":"environ 1130","1170":"1170","about 1197":"environ 1197","1229":"1229","1070":"1070","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, France","lifeSummary":"William de Bendeng est né environ 1130, fils de de Bendeng. Il a épousé Gunnora environ 1165. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé environ 1197, à l’âge de 69 ans."},"de":{"about 1130–about 1197":"um 1130–um 1197","1129–1190":"1129–1190","1130–1197":"1130–1197","1070–1158":"1070–1158","1170–1229":"1170–1229","–Male":"Verstorben","1190":"1190","1129":"1129","about 1170":"um 1170","1158":"1158","1197":"1197","1130":"1130","about 1165":"um 1165","about 1130":"um 1130","1170":"1170","about 1197":"um 1197","1229":"1229","1070":"1070","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Fran